Content derived from the **D&D 5th Edition Systems Reference Document (SRD)** is licensed under CC BY 4.0 by Wizards of the Coast:

[![CC BY 4.0](https://i.creativecommons.org/l/by/4.0/88x31.png)](http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/)

**Required Attribution:**
```
This work includes material taken from the System Reference Document 5.1 ("SRD 5.1")
by Wizards of the Coast LLC and available at https://dnd.wizards.com/resources/systems-reference-document.
The SRD 5.1 is licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International License
available at https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/legalcode.
```

**SRD Content Includes:**
- D&D 5e rules, classes, races, spells, monsters, and items from the official SRD
- See `docs/third-party/SRD_5.1_LICENSE.md` for the complete SRD license

### Public Domain Content (CC0 1.0)

Some content in this repository is dedicated to the **Public Domain** under CC0 1.0:

[![CC0](https://licensebuttons.net/p/zero/1.0/88x31.png)](https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/)

**Applies to:**
- Third-party public domain content (`data/cc0/`)
- Public domain assets (`public/assets/cc0/`)
- Content explicitly marked as CC0

**Usage**: No attribution required (though ethically recommended)

**Note**: CC0 content can be freely incorporated into works under any license (Apache 2.0, MIT, CC BY 4.0, proprietary, etc.)

### Other Third-Party Licenses

**Foundry VTT Integration:**
- Foundry VTT software is proprietary and requires a license from Foundry Gaming LLC
- This repository does NOT include Foundry VTT source code
- Integration is via documented APIs only
- See: https://foundryvtt.com/article/license/

**Worldographer:**
- Worldographer software is proprietary and requires a license from Inkwell Ideas
- This repository does NOT include Worldographer source code
- See: https://worldographer.com/

## 4. Proprietary Assets & IP (All Rights Reserved)

The following assets and intellectual property are **NOT licensed** under any open source license and remain the exclusive property of Crit-Fumble:

### ðŸš« NOT Licensed (All Rights Reserved)

**Visual Assets:**
- Crit-Fumble logo and branding
- Custom artwork and illustrations
- Character portraits (non-SRD)
- UI graphics and icons (custom)
- Map assets (custom)
- Video content
- Animated assets

**Audio Assets:**
- Sound effects (custom)
- Music compositions (custom)
- Voiceovers and audio recordings

**Proprietary Game Content:**
- Original game systems and mechanics (non-SRD)
- Proprietary adventure modules
- Campaign settings (unless explicitly CC BY 4.0)
- Unique character concepts and lore
- Proprietary monster/creature designs
- Custom magic items and artifacts

**Branding & Trademarks:**
- "Crit-Fumble" name and logo
- Taglines and slogans
- Visual identity and brand guidelines
- Domain names

**Location:**
These proprietary assets are typically located in:
- `/public/assets/proprietary/` (if present)
- `/public/audio/` (custom audio)
- `/public/video/` (custom video)
- Marked with `Â© All Rights Reserved` or similar

### How to Identify Proprietary Assets

Proprietary assets will typically include one of:
1. Copyright notice: `Â© 2025 Crit-Fumble. All Rights Reserved.`
2. Located in `/proprietary/` directories
3. Explicitly marked in metadata or file headers
4. Listed in `ASSETS.md` (if present)

### Using Proprietary Assets

To use proprietary assets, you must:
1. Contact: legal@crit-fumble.com
2. Obtain written permission
3. Negotiate licensing terms

**Exception:** If you're running your own instance of Crit-Fumble for personal/non-commercial use, you may use the default assets included in the repository, but you may NOT:
- Redistribute the assets separately
- Use them in other projects
- Create derivative works
- Use them commercially without permission

