## How to Comply

### If you're using Apache 2.0 code (core business logic):
1. Include the Apache 2.0 license text (LICENSE-APACHE)
2. Include copyright notice in NOTICE file
3. Preserve SPDX headers in source files

### If you're using MIT code (UI components):
1. Include the MIT license text (LICENSE-MIT)
2. Preserve copyright notice in source files

### If you're using the original content:
1. Provide attribution: "Content from Crit-Fumble (https://crit-fumble.com)"
2. Link to CC BY 4.0 license

### If you're using 5e SRD content:
1. Provide attribution to Wizards of the Coast (see required text above)
2. Maintain CC BY 4.0 license

### If you're using everything:
1. Include the Apache 2.0 license for code
2. Provide attribution for content: "Powered by Crit-Fumble (https://crit-fumble.com)"
3. Include SRD attribution if using D&D 5e content

